{"name": "mosaic-queen", "metadata": {"name": "mosaic-queen", "version": "1.1.1", "classifiers": [], "home_page": "https://github.com/caracal-pipeline/MosaicQueen", "license": "", "documentation_url": null, "dependencies": ["numpy", "astropy", "memory-profiler", "matplotlib", "scipy"], "summary": "A package with mosaicking commands from montage", "upload_time": 1655389656}, "documentation": ["---\nsubstitutions:\n  Pypi Version: |-\n    ```{image} https://img.shields.io/pypi/v/mosaic-queen.svg\n    :alt: true\n    :target: https://pypi.org/project/mosaic-queen/\n    ```\n---\n\n# MosaicQueen\n\n{{ Pypi Version }}\n\nA package with mosaicking commands from montage, that also does primary-beam correction for both 2D and 3D images. Originally written to be used by stimela (<https://github.com/SpheMakh/Stimela>) and, ultimately, CARACal (<https://github.com/caracal-pipeline/caracal>) for automated radio-data reduction, but it also works independently.\n\n# Installation\n\nFirst install montage via\n\n```bash\nsudo apt install montage\n```\n\nPackage is available on PyPI (<https://pypi.org/project/mosaic-queen>) and so it is installable via\n\n```bash\npip install mosaic-queen\n```\n\nWork in progress: convolution of input images to a common synthesised beam before mosaicking, and employing parallel processing to speed this up...\n"], "modules": [{"name": "mosaicqueen.main", "documentation": ["!/usr/bin/env python", "------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------", "Authors of package: Sarah White (sarahwhite.astro@gmail.com)", "Sphe Makhathini (sphemakh@gmail.com)", "Paolo Serra (paolo.serra@inaf.it)", "------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------"], "functions": [{"name": "mosaicqueen.main.check_for_files", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "directory", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "fits_files", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": 